# Test Environment Configuration
# ================================
# This test environment runs alongside your production stack.
# It uses a separate MongoDB and Redis for the test backend,
# while connecting to your already-running production Payload CMS.
#
# PREREQUISITE: Run production first!
#   ./scripts/run-prod.sh -d
#
# Then start test environment:
#   ./scripts/run-test.sh -d

# =============================================================================
# No configuration required!
# =============================================================================
# The test environment automatically:
#   - Uses production Payload CMS at localhost:3001
#   - Creates isolated test MongoDB (mongodb_test:27017)
#   - Creates isolated test Redis (redis_test:6379)
#
# Your GOOGLE_API_KEY is loaded from ./backend/.env

# =============================================================================
# Optional: Override test URLs (usually not needed)
# =============================================================================
# TEST_BACKEND_URL=http://localhost:8001
# TEST_PAYLOAD_URL=http://localhost:3001
